A few years ago, I was in Puglia Italy and, with the help of social media and some internet friends, was able to locate the exact location of the displaced persons camp my grandfather “Papa” was at after World War II - Santa Maria Al Bagno. Today, my dad and mom were able to make the same trip! 3 Generations, 2 speedos (dad left his at home), 1 magical location that must gave been a little piece of heaven for all the refugees including my Papa.

“Let’s do a Chaos Dinner?!” What started as a kernel of an idea - bring @evanrosskatz’s Instagram feed to life - became a reality last night. The goal: celebrate Evan’s unique ability to catapult memeable moments into the zeitgeist, and those who help provide him with the material in the first place all powered by @threads. Thank you thank you thank you Evan for your partnership - building this “moment” with you was not work, it was so wildly fun and… chaotic! Special shoutout to @charlesporch Sibyl & @claudine for trusting me with this bonkers idea, @crystalkungminkoff for opening her home and hosting everyone, @carlycoelet @etrems @andygelb and the whole team at SLATE for locking arms with me and building this GORGESSICA event. This project was a pie-in-the-sky dream come to life ✨
